# (git 3) Analysis I (<i>F<sub>ST</sub></i> & GxP)

## Summary

The genetic differentiation, as well as the genotype x phenotype association, are computed within the [**nextflow**](https://www.nextflow.io/) script `analysis_fst_gxp.nf` (located under `$BASE_DIR/nf/03_analysis_fst_gxp/`).
It takes the _SNPs only_ data set and computes _F<sub>ST</sub>_ and the GxP association.
Below is an overview of the steps involved in the analysis.
(The <span style="color:#4DAF4A">green dot</span> indicates the genotype input, <span style="color:#E41A1C">red arrows</span> depict output that is exported for further use.)

## Details of `analysis_fst_gxp.nf`

### Setup

The nextflow script starts by opening the genotype data and feeding it into three different streams.

<div class="kclass">

<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode">#<span class="hl opt">!/</span>usr<span class="hl opt">/</span>bin<span class="hl opt">/</span>env nextflow
<span class="hl slc">// git 3.1</span>
<span class="hl slc">// open genotype data</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.fromFilePairs<span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;../../1_genotyping/4_phased/phased_mac2.vcf.{gz,gz.tbi}&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.into<span class="hl opt">{</span> vcf_locations<span class="hl opt">;</span> vcf_filter<span class="hl opt">;</span> vcf_gxp<span class="hl opt">;</span> vcf_adapt <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Since we are going to work on the three sampling locations independently, we create channel for the locations.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.2</span>
<span class="hl slc">// initialize location channel</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;bel&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;hon&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;pan&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> locations_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Then we attach the genotypes to the locations.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.3</span>
<span class="hl slc">// attach genotypes to location</span>
locations_ch
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_locations <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> vcf_location_combo <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Next, we define the species sets sampled at the individual locations.

### <i>F<sub>ST</sub></i>

Using this subset, we compute the global differentiation among all hamlet populations.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// ----------- Fst section -----------</span>

<span class="hl kwa">process</span> fst_multi <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_20g15h_fst_multi&#39;</span>

Then, we set up the pair wise species comparisons...


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.8</span>
<span class="hl slc">// prepare pairwise fsts</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ------------------------------</span>
<span class="hl com">/* (create all possible species pairs depending on location</span>
<span class="hl com">   and combine with genotype subset (for the respective location))*/</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ------------------------------</span>
<span class="hl com">/* channel content after joinig:</span>
<span class="hl com">  set [0:val(loc), 1:file(vcf), 2:file(pop), 3:val(spec1), 4:val(spec2)]*/</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ------------------------------</span>
bel_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;bel&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.join<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_loc_pair1 <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>bel_spec1_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>bel_spec2_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">5</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">6</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
hon_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;hon&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.join<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_loc_pair2 <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>hon_spec1_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>hon_spec2_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">5</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">6</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
pan_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;pan&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.join<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_loc_pair3 <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>pan_spec1_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>pan_spec2_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">5</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">6</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
bel_pairs_ch.concat<span class="hl opt">(</span> hon_pairs_ch<span class="hl opt">,</span> pan_pairs_ch  <span class="hl opt">)</span>.set <span class="hl opt">{</span> all_fst_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

... and run them.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.9</span>
<span class="hl slc">// compute pairwise fsts</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> fst_run <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_32g4h_fst_run&#39;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/fst/50k/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">,</span> pattern<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.50k.windowed.weir.fst.gz&quot;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/fst/10k/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">,</span> pattern<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.10k.windowed.weir.fst.gz&quot;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/fst/logs/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">,</span> pattern<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${loc}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2}</span><span class="hl str">.log&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> loc <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> pop <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> spec1 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> spec2 <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> all_fst_pairs_ch

<span class="hl str">	vcftools --gzvcf</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>

<span class="hl str">		--weir-fst-pop pop2.txt \</span>

### GxP

The software use for the GxP association uses genotypes in `plink` file format, so the first step was to convert the input.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// ----------- G x P section -----------</span>

<span class="hl slc">// git 3.11</span>
<span class="hl slc">// reformat genotypes (1)</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> plink12 <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_20g2h_plink12&#39;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> vcfId<span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> vcf_gxp

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;GxP_plink.map&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;GxP_plink.ped&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> plink_GxP

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	vcfsamplenames</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">| \</span>
<span class="hl str">		grep -v &quot;tor</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">|tab</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">|flo&quot; | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		awk &#39;{print \$1&quot;</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t&quot;\$1}&#39; | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		sed &#39;s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t.*</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">(...</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">)</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">(...</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">)\$/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">1</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">2/g&#39; &gt; pop.txt</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	vcftools \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--gzvcf</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>
<span class="hl str">		--plink \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--out GxP_plink</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	plink \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--file GxP_plink \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--recode12 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--out hapmap</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>

<span class="hl slc">// git 3.12</span>
<span class="hl slc">// reformat genotypes (2)</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> GxP_run <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_20g2h_GxP_binary&#39;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> map <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> ped <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> plink_GxP

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.bed&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.bim&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span><span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.fam&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> plink_binary

Having collected all the input, we can now run the GxP.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.17</span>
<span class="hl slc">// actually run the GxP</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> gemma_run <span class="hl opt">{</span>
 <span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_32g4h_GxP_run&#39;</span>
 <span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/GxP/bySNP/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span>
 <span class="hl slc">//module &quot;R3.5.2&quot;</span>

 <span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
 <span class="hl kwa">set</span>  <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> pheno <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> bed <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> bim <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> fam <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> pheno_file <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> trait_plink_combo

 <span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
 <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;*.GxP.txt.gz&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> gemma_results

 <span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	source \$BASE_DIR/sh/body.sh</span>
<span class="hl str">	BASE_NAME=\$(echo</span>  <span class="hl ipl">${fam}</span> <span class="hl str">| sed &#39;s/.fam//g&#39;)</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	mv</span> <span class="hl ipl">${fam}</span> <span class="hl str">\$BASE_NAME-old.fam</span>
<span class="hl str">	cp \</span><span class="hl ipl">${BASE_NAME}</span><span class="hl str">-old.fam</span> <span class="hl ipl">${fam}</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	# 1) replace the phenotype values</span>
<span class="hl str">	Rscript --vanilla \$BASE_DIR/R/assign_phenotypes.R</span> <span class="hl ipl">${fam} ${pheno_file} ${pheno}</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	# 2) create relatedness matrix of samples using gemma</span>
<span class="hl str">	gemma -bfile \$BASE_NAME -gk 1 -o</span> <span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	# 3) fit linear model using gemma (-lm)</span>
<span class="hl str">	gemma -bfile \$BASE_NAME -lm 4 -miss 0.1 -notsnp -o</span> <span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.lm</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	# 4) fit linear mixed model using gemma (-lmm)</span>
<span class="hl str">	gemma -bfile \$BASE_NAME -k output/</span><span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.cXX.txt -lmm 4 -o</span> <span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.lmm</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	# 5) reformat output</span>
<span class="hl str">	sed &#39;s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">trs</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">tCHROM</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">tPOS</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/g; s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">([0-2][0-9]</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">):/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">1</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/g&#39; output/</span><span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.lm.assoc.txt | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		cut -f 2,3,9-14 | body sort -k1,1 -k2,2n | gzip &gt;</span> <span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.lm.GxP.txt.gz</span>
<span class="hl str">	sed &#39;s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">trs</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">tCHROM</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">tPOS</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/g; s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">([0-2][0-9]</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">):/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">1</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/g&#39; output/</span><span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.lmm.assoc.txt | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		cut -f 2,3,8-10,13-15 | body sort -k1,1 -k2,2n | gzip &gt;</span> <span class="hl ipl">${pheno}</span><span class="hl str">.lmm.GxP.txt.gz</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

To smooth the GxP results, we initialize two resolutions (50 kb windows with 5 kb increments and 10 kb windows with 1 kb increments).


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.18</span>
<span class="hl slc">// setup smoothing levels</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">([[</span><span class="hl num">50000</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl num">5000</span><span class="hl opt">], [</span><span class="hl num">10000</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl num">1000</span><span class="hl opt">]])</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> gxp_smoothing_levels <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The we apply all smoothing levels to the raw GxP output...


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.19</span>
<span class="hl slc">// apply all smoothing levels</span>
gemma_results.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> gxp_smoothing_levels <span class="hl opt">)</span>.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> gxp_smoothing_input <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

.. and run the smoothing.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.20</span>
<span class="hl slc">// actually run the smoothing</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> gemma_smooth <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_20g2h_GxP_smooth&#39;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/GxP/</span><span class="hl ipl">${win}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> lm <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> lmm <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> win <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> step <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> gxp_smoothing_input

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> win <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.lm.*k.txt.gz&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> gxp_lm_smoothing_output
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> win <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.lmm.*k.txt.gz&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> gxp_lmm_smoothing_output

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	\$BASE_DIR/sh/gxp_slider</span> <span class="hl ipl">${lm} ${win} ${step}</span>
<span class="hl str">	\$BASE_DIR/sh/gxp_slider</span> <span class="hl ipl">${lmm} ${win} ${step}</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

At this step we are done with differentiation and GxP.

### <i>F<sub>ST</sub></i> within species (adaptation scenario)

To judge the independence of the individual populations of the hamlets species sampled at several locations,
we also compute the <i>F<sub>ST</sub></i> among those populations.
We start by defining the species-set for which we sampled multiple populations.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// Fst within species ---------------------------------------------------------</span>
<span class="hl slc">// git 3.21</span>
<span class="hl slc">// define species set</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;nig&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;pue&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;uni&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> species_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Then, we define the sampling locations.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.22</span>
<span class="hl slc">// define location set</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">( [[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;bel&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">], [</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;hon&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">], [</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;pan&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">]])</span>.into<span class="hl opt">{</span> locations_ch_1<span class="hl opt">;</span>locations_ch_2 <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Next, we create all population-pairs and bind it to the genotype file.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.23</span>
<span class="hl slc">// create location pairs</span>
locations_ch_1
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>locations_ch_2<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> species_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_adapt <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> vcf_location_combo_adapt <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Last, we compute the pair wise <i>F<sub>ST</sub></i> among all populations.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 3.24</span>
<span class="hl slc">// compute pairwise fsts</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> fst_run_adapt <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_20g4h_fst_run_adapt&#39;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/fst/adapt/&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span> <span class="hl opt">,</span> pattern<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.log&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> loc1 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> loc2 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> spec <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span>vcf_indx<span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> vcf_location_combo_adapt

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;adapt_</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc1}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc2}</span><span class="hl str">.log&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> fst_adapt_logs

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	vcfsamplenames</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">| grep</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc1}</span> <span class="hl str">&gt; pop1.txt</span>
<span class="hl str">	vcfsamplenames</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">| grep</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc2}</span> <span class="hl str">&gt; pop2.txt</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	vcftools --gzvcf</span> <span class="hl ipl">${vcf[0]}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>
<span class="hl str">		--weir-fst-pop pop1.txt \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--weir-fst-pop pop2.txt \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--out adapt_</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc1}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc2}</span> <span class="hl str">2&gt; adapt_</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc1}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}${loc2}</span><span class="hl str">.log</span>
<span class="hl str">	&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>
</div>
